# Fix Google Sign-In "Cancelled" Error

## Goal
Resolve the "cancelled" error during Google Sign-In by ensuring the correct scopes are requested. The application relies on Google Drive for storage (as seen in [DriveService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/drive_service.dart#10-247) and [LoginScreen](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/login_screen.dart#11-17) debug prints), but [AuthService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart#5-49) currently initializes `GoogleSignIn` without any scopes. This mismatch often leads to authentication failures or subsequent permission errors.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change adds the `drive.driveFileScope` to the Google Sign-In request. Users will see a permission prompt asking for access to Google Drive files. This is expected and necessary for the app to function.

## Proposed Changes

### Auth Service
#### [MODIFY] [auth_service.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart)
- Initialize `GoogleSignIn` with `scopes: [drive.DriveApi.driveFileScope]`.
- This ensures the user is prompted for Drive access during sign-in.

### Login Screen
#### [MODIFY] [login_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/login_screen.dart)
- Improve error handling to print more details to the console if sign-in returns failure.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Run the app on the device (iOS).
2.  Tap "Sign in with Google Drive".
3.  **Expectation**: The system consent dialog appears ("'Rozze' wants to use google.com to sign in").
4.  Tap Continue.
5.  **Expectation**: The Google Sign-In sheet appears. Select an account.
6.  **Expectation**: A new permission screen appears asking for access to Drive files.
7.  Allow the permissions.
8.  **Expectation**: Sign-in succeeds, and the app navigates to the main screen.

### Automated Tests
- None (Authentication flow requires user interaction).
